# Cursor AI Repository Rules

GOAL
Preserve product behavior, logic, and APIs at all times.

ABSOLUTE DO-NOTs
- Do not change business logic or control flow
- Do not change public APIs or request/response formats
- Do not rename or delete existing functions, classes, files, or exports
- Do not introduce new dependencies
- Do not modify environment variables or configuration keys

ALLOWED CHANGES (SAFE ONLY)
- Fix compiler or type errors without changing runtime behavior
- Fix lint issues that do not affect logic
- Remove unused imports or unreachable dead code (only if provable)
- Add missing types or annotations
- Fix clearly broken typings

EDITING RULES
- Prefer minimal, localized changes
- Limit edits to files explicitly mentioned or clearly required
- Avoid multi-file edits unless strictly necessary
- If unsure about safety, do NOT apply the change

WORKFLOW
- Scan before editing unfamiliar code
- Summarize what was changed and what was intentionally not changed
